cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.IR

The paper deals with image super-resolution using a convolutional neural network, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of deep learning techniques for this task also suggests the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of data from different geographical locations and land-cover types, which suggests the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with remote sensing data, which suggests the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
